<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 6:09PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN CHARLOTTE AND
EASTERN HALIFAX COUNTIES THROUGH 645 PM EDT...
At 609 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dryburg, or 8 miles east of South Boston, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
South Boston...
Redoak...
Clover...
Scottsburg...
Hitesburg...
Mt Laurel...
and Staunton River State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
